<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-72-0778 </DOCNO><TEXT>Worldwide, biomass-derived energy is six times as much as that derivedfrom hydro and nuclear energy combined. With the long history of use,it is interesting that biomass energy is so poorly understood that seriouscontroversy still exists. Many points of disagreement result from differencesin perceptions and inadequacy of the data used in analyses of biomasstechnologies and opportunities, including problems pertaining to environmentalconsiderations relating to biomass energy development.</TEXT></DOC>